Once an order is placed by the customer , it undergoes various stages till it is delivered to the customer .The various states of an order Â from the time of order placement till the delivery to customer Â is known as Forward Process .

&nbsp;

<strong>Order States: Forward Process</strong>

<a href="http://localhost/paytmbigbo/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Order-States-Forward-Process1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1567" src="http://localhost/paytmbigbo/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Order-States-Forward-Process1.jpg" alt="Order-States--Forward-Process" width="1004" height="625" /></a>
<ol>
	<li><em><strong>Pending Acknowledgement</strong>Â :</em>In this state, the seller receives the order request. The seller can check the availability of inventory one last time before accepting the order.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Pending Shipment :</strong></em>In this state, the seller has accepted the order. The order is yet to be packed.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Shipment created :</strong></em>The seller packs the order according to pre decided Â Paytm guidelines. Invoices are attached to the package. The intimation for the order goes to the courier partner as well.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Manifest Created</strong></em> :The final list of products to be shipped is tabulated and invoices are printed out and attached to the order. The delivery partner collects the package from the seller shop or warehouse.</li>
	<li><em><strong>SEED scan</strong></em>Â :When the order reaches the SEED from the merchants . (For merchants tagged under SEED network)
<em><strong>SEED shipped</strong></em>Â :When the courier partner collects the order from the SEED.(For merchants tagged under SEED network). <a href="http://localhost/paytmbigbo/seed/">More on SEED</a></li>
	<li><em><strong>Shipped :</strong></em>The order is scanned and shipped to the customer from the delivery partner warehouse.(When seller is not under SEED network).<a href="http://localhost/paytmbigbo/seed/">More on SEED</a></li>
	<li><em><strong>Delivered :</strong></em>In this state the delivery partner delivers the product to the customer.</li>
</ol>
The various states of an order Â from the time a return is requested by the customer till Â the delivery to the merchantÂ  is known as ReverseÂ Process .

&nbsp;

<strong>Order States: Reverse Process</strong>

<a href="http://localhost/paytmbigbo/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Order-States-Reverse-Process1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1568" src="http://localhost/paytmbigbo/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Order-States-Reverse-Process1.jpg" alt="Order-States--Reverse-Process" width="1004" height="625" /></a>
<ol>
	<li><em><strong>Return Requested:</strong></em> In this stage, the customer has raised a return request for the order.Â It marks the beginning of the return flow.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Return Rejected:</strong></em> The return request of the customer is rejected which might be due to some pre-defined reason. this stage leads to a closure of the returns process for the order.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Return Accepted:</strong></em> The return request is accepted in this stage and the courier partner (in case the Seller is LMD) is intimated of this.</li>
	<li><strong><em>Return Picked:</em></strong> The stage arrives once the courier partner has picked up the parcel from the customerâ€™s premise. The Seller gets a notification at this stage.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Received at RPC</strong></em>: This stage marks the parcel reaching one of the Paytmâ€™s Reverse Processing Centers (RPCs) for quality check purpose.</li>
	<li><em><strong>Shipped From RPC:</strong></em> This stage occurs once the product has passed the quality checks at the assigned RPC and has been dispatched to the Seller.</li>
	<li><strong><em>Liquidated:</em></strong> It marks the phase when the returnedÂ product fails the quality checks at the assigned RPC and is sent for liquidation. This represents the closure of the return process.</li>
	<li><strong><em>Return Delivered</em></strong>: Once the parcel gets delivered back to the Seller, the status/ stage changes to Return Delivered. This marks the end of the returns flow.</li>
</ol>";s:10:"post_title";s:6:"Stages";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:6:"stages";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-10-21 10:08:04";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-21 10:08:04";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://localhost/paytmbigbo/?page_id=398";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}